column5: Open seat for muskie... I have all the gear. Meet in London 5am, back to London mid-afternoon (flexible) Just bring snacks/beverages for yourself and help out with the expense.  Brian
Dang, hope someone jumps on this quick! Wish I was closer. Very kind of you Brian.
You should make the trip someday Roy. BTW, Don and Ruth are going to be down your way next week with Marc.
Wish I was closer too Brian... I'd jump on this in a heartbeat    But infortunitely, tomorrow I'm going to our hunting grounds to check on the territory and bring food for the deers
Wish I could, already have plans
Hmmm. If I left now, lol ! Came back last night to all my customers aircraft parked on the driveway in front of the hangar door... so I guess I'm out! Have fun Brian, someone will jump on it.
LOL Wayne, playing Cessna Tetris again?

Pretty much... just prefer when they come in one at a time, so that I can do the maintenance and then put them in their winter blocking spots one at a time. Everyone saw the sun on Tuesday and did a panic flight direct to here. One even paid for a taxi ride back to Toronto to do so.
Come play with smallies Brian.  Never mind,the pros caught them all.LOL
I'd be tempted......but I'm going to hold out for a weekend here shortly  Good Luck Brian
